docs.lead_paragraph: THESE 16 essays, presented by a group of scholars to honor a member of their guild at the University of Southern California, have a great deal of charm, are wonderfully relaxing, and are entertaining in the best sense. This is so even though the essays are less unified in theme than is usually true in such collections.
